http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/kolkata/Army-man-allegedly-misbehaves-with-woman-on-train-held/article13992000.ece

An Army man has been arrested at the Mughalsarai railway station for allegedly “misbehaving” with a woman passenger who was travelling with him in Howrah-New Delhi Rajdhani Express, a Railway official said here on Saturday.The incident came close on the heels of a gang-rape of a minor girl in a train allegedly by two para-military personnel.The accused identified as Lance Naik Diler Singh, who is posted at Agartala, was arrested by the Government Railway Police (GRP) of Mughalsarai late last night for allegedly “misbehaving” with the woman travelling in the same B3 coach of Howrah-New Delhi Rajdhani Express, the Eastern Railway officer told PTI.An FIR was lodged against Singh under IPC Section 354 (assault or criminal force to woman with intent to outrage her modesty).Earlier on December 28, an Army jawan forced a minor girl to consume alcohol who was later gang-raped allegedly by two paramilitary force personnel inside a compartment, reserved for security personnel, of the Howrah-Amritsar Express.She was later rescued by RPF in Madhupur station in Jharkhand.The three accused were subsequently arrested and identified by the victim. -